name: hydra
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Hydra" %}
{% set version = "2.5" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: 247091b9c279c77686ea995f0f07070a28870c1942959b1474ad57076074384a

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [win]
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  build:
    - '{{ compiler("c") }}'
  host:
    - python
    - cython >=0.24
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - hydra

about:
  home: "http://github.com/crankycoder/Hydra"
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: license.txt
  summary: "A high performance persistent bloom filter"
  doc_url: "https://github.com/crankycoder/Hydra"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/crankycoder/Hydra"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - luizirber
